Oh my! First I have to say that I bake a lot of cheesecakes - they are my husband's favorite & after 13 years I've gotten quite adept, and become pretty well-known for my cheesecakes. I also should point out that I don't usually like WHITE chocolate. With that said, this was THE ABSOLUTE BEST CHEESECAKE I HAVE EVER MADE...and that's saying a lot, considering I have made hundreds! The white chocolate added a luxurious creaminess above usual cheesecake. The flavor was very subtle, and adds a stronger vanilla flavor. I suggest trying other flavors of jelly - I used seedless raspberry & added a tsp or 2 of sugar because it was tart. The reddish color really added to the beauty of the berries. One note: To make ahead, don't add strawberries until just before serving. And, if possible, allow cheesecake to sit out & take off the chill - the flavor will improve. Once the fruit is added, this will NOT keep well longer than 24 hours, so plan accordingly. I gave the leftovers to my (very happy, appreciative) neighbors. Once the berries & glaze are added, they will begin to break down quickly. You won't be disappointed, try this amazing recipe!

