We made this cheesecake in our culinary arts class. We made two of these cakes and they were both very good. The thing about this cake is that it rises a lot! So make sure you keep the top of the cheesecake away from the main source of heat or you will burn the top of the it. Also in the directions it never specificaly stated when we were suppose to add in the white chocolate so we decided to put it in the filling. This made the cheesecake jiggly when it was suppose to be done cooking so we let the cake cool and then put it in the refridgerator. The next day when we got the cake out it had fallen a little, but not much. We changed the recipe by making a thinner apricot glaze. We put the apricot preserves in a blender added a little sugar and blended it. then we put the apricot glaze on the side of the cake so that the strawberrys would stick to the side. Then we creatively decorated the top of the cake. We then made a strawberry glaze by putting strawberries and sugar in the blender and drizzling it on top along with the apricot glaze that we had made. The cake turned out beautifully! It was very summery looking and very delicious!

