Rating: 4
I have made this recipe as written several times, and it is to die for - my favorite cheesecake recipe ever. I just made it for a holiday party and, with fresh strawberries unavailable, had to come up with an alternative -- it turned out good enough to share: after the cheesecake had chilled overnight, I "depanned" it and set the bottom of the springform pan on a cooling rack. I made a ganache out of 1 cup heavy whipping cream, 8 oz. of 60% cacao bittersweet chocolate, and about 1 1/2 Tbs. of sugar. After the ganache cooled a bit, I poured it over the cheesecake, dripping it down the sides and spreading to cover completely (this made a hideous mess, but whatever). After a few hours, the chocolate firmed into a glossy chocolate shell. It really rocked - the dark chocolate was a great foil for the delicate, creamy cheesecake. And it was pretty too. :)

