Rating: 4
i made this but with a lot of changes... first, i made this a white chocolate raspberry cheesecake but instead of putting the fruit on top i made a coulis by cooking the fruit with sugar, pureeing, and straining... and i swirled this into the cheesecake batter right before baking. i decorated the top with white chocolate curls and whipped cream. next, instead of using the full amount of sour cream, i used 1/2 cup sour cream and added 1/4 cup heavy cream. and lastly, i baked this first at 500ºF for 10 min. and then lowered the temp to 200ºF for 1 1/2 hours. i only did this because i read that this way it becomes more like a NY dense cheesecake and i read the reviews about it being very light and creamy but i like it dense.. anyway, it came out with a lot of cracks so maybe next time i will just try the regular baking directions. despite that, it came out awesome and everyone LOVED it. maybe next time i'll try the recipe as is, but i'm still very happy with how it turned out. :)

