I really liked this recipe, and would definitely make it again with a couple of changes: 1) the white chocolate I used was way too strong (Trader Joe's white chocolate chips). It actually overpowered the cake. I'll either use less or change brands. 2) I think the cooking time is a little off (but I guess this depends on the oven). I'd probably leave it in for another 10-15 minutes, as the cake was a little soft and gooey when it was cut. Everyone raved, though! I brought this and the carrot cake with maple cream cheese icing to a birthday party, and the cheesecake was the first to go. It looked very nice and professional - just like the photo. I especially loved the "height" of the cake. It reminded me of something you'd see in a gourmet bakery. All-in-all, a wonderful recipe that makes for a light and creamy consistency, a beautiful presentation, and very happy guests! One more thing...make sure that the cake is completely cooled before refrigerating it. I started out with no cracks on top, but a couple formed as it cooled in the fridge. I guess it really doesn't matter, though, since the gorgeous strawberry topping covers up any boo-boos.

