My culinary friends know me as "Cheesecake King", but I have never received more compliments than on this one. I made it for the first time last Easter to rave reviews. I usually like to adjust recipes to my own taste, but not this one. If you decide to make it, don't change a thing. However, it is a lot of batter for a 9" springform pan. To ensure that it bakes to completion without cracking, I would suggest cutting the baking time by about 15 minutes, turning the oven off, and allowing it to cool in the oven with the door open for about one hour. The strawberries with the brandy-apricot glaze taste heavenly and make a spectacular presentation. This is definitely an elegant and refreshing warm-weather dessert. This is also a pretty easy recipe if you are dabbling in cheesecakes for the first time. Hey, if you crack it, no one will ever know, anyway.

