The most delicious cheesecake I have ever made! It does, however require a slightly larger pan or division between two. It should also be baked a little longer, 10-20 minutes,you don't want as much movement as suggested in the recipe. Add 25 degrees to the oven temperature for high altitudes. The best tip would be to place a pan(a 9" x 13" cake or a larger jelly roll) with at least one inch of water in it on the oven shelf below the one on which you place the cheesecake for baking. This keeps the oven moist enough to help prevent the cake from cracking. The strawberries are just as delicious on the side!

